messages.content: You are tasked with creating a structured output from the provided user message.

- Full HTTP request path:
  /cms/admin/group

- All HTTP methods acceptable: false

- HEAD: false

- POST: true

- OPTIONS: false

- TRACE: false

- GET: false

- PUT: false

- DELETE: false

- PATCH: false

Explanation:
- The create_group handler is registered on the admin_api blueprint with @admin_api.route("/group", methods=["POST"]). That restricts the route to the POST method in the source code.
- The admin_api blueprint is registered under the cms blueprint with url_prefix="/admin" (app/api/cms/__init__.py), and the cms blueprint is itself registered on the application with url_prefix="/cms" (app/__init__.py). Combining the prefixes gives the full path /cms + /admin + /group â†’ /cms/admin/group.
- Because the route decorator explicitly specifies methods=["POST"], only POST is indicated as acceptable by the code. The other methods (HEAD, OPTIONS, TRACE, GET, PUT, DELETE, PATCH) are not declared in the route definition, so they are reported as not acceptable based strictly on the code.
